data.title: Over-height truck blocks Sydney Harbour Tunnel for second time today
data.meta_description: Another oversized truck has caused traffic delays by blocking the entrance to the Sydney Harbour Tunnel for...
data.text:
Another over-height truck has caused traffic delays by blocking the entrance to the Sydney Harbour Tunnel for the second time today.

Cars were stopped from going south through the tunnel under the Sydney Harbour Bridge after sensors were triggered by a truck on the Warringah Freeway just before 6pm.

The lanes were reopened about an hour later during peak evening traffic.

A different truck triggered the same sensors in a near identical incident at 7.48 this morning.

Both trucks were made to reverse and move into the slip lane by Traffic and Highway patrol officers, who were called to the scene.

Police investigators and the National Heavy Vehicle Regulator are enquiring with the drivers.

It is a $5500 fine for triggering the sensors and will cost drivers 12 demerit points.
